.SH "Detailed Description"
.PP 
the object to manage an array of \fI\fBMqBufferS\fP\fP items. 

every \fI\fBMqBufferLS\fP\fP is able to store a infinite number of \fI\fBMqBufferS\fP\fP objects using dynamic allocation. the \fI\fBMqBufferS\fP\fP objects are stored in a flat array of \fI\fBMqBufferS\fP\fP object pointers. to access an object only the \fIdata\fP or the \fIcur\fP member is used (e.g. \fB\fCdata\fP[index\fP]). in difference to the \fIdata\fP member the \fIcur\fP member has a floating position to implement an increment/decrement like behaviour 
.PP
